{
  "stem": "2916.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So, I personally don't have specific recollections.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But for me, it was a very, very, happy memory, my childhood, before the Hungarian occupation.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father, my mother, and I have an older brother.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We also had an aunt, my mother's oldest sister, who lived in town, some 8 to 10 minute walk from our house.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she practically was part of our family.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She was there at festive meals.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "At the Sabbath Eves, she ate with us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "She was practically part of our family.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then, both my mother and my father's family, brothers and sisters, lived in Hungary, which was even though it was quite near the other side of the Danube, but the two countries were not friendly to each other.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And so the travel wasn't that easy.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "People had to apply for a passport and a visa.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And a visa was not always easy to get, so that the visits between my extended family and us weren't frequent.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Possibly once a year, my mother's brothers and one sister would come to our town.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Because my grandparents were buried there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Meaning, their parents were buried.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And it is a Jewish custom to go at least once a year to pay respect to the departed.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So this I remember as a child, that all my uncles would come and my aunt from Hungary at least once a year.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father's brother, my father had one younger brother, he went to America, to New York, when I was a very, very little girl.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I never met him until after the war when I got here.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then he had a sister, who had a very large family.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she had never come to us.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
